Appendix B: Financial Model Assumptions and Sensitivity Analyses

This appendix outlines the core assumptions behind the Levelized Cost of Energy (LCOE), Levelized Cost of Hydrogen (LCOH), and project-level financial models referenced in Chapters 6 and 7.

B.1 Base Case Assumptions (All figures in real 2024 USD)

· Discount Rate (WACC): 7.0% for project finance (reflecting blended cost of senior debt at 5% and equity return expectation of 10%).
· Project Life: 25 years for PV and Wind plants; 20 years for electrolyzer stacks (with one replacement at Year 10).
· Capital Expenditure (CAPEX):
  · Utility-Scale PV: $0.50/Wdc
  · Onshore Wind: $1.10/W
  ·  Li-ion Battery Storage (4-hour system): $250/kWh
  · Alkaline Electrolyzer (including balance of plant): $500/kW
  · Green Ammonia Synthesis Plant (Haber-Bosch): $800/ton annual capacity
· Operational Expenditure (OPEX):
  · PV: 1.5% of CAPEX/year
  · Wind: 2.5% of CAPEX/year
  · Electrolyzer: 3% of CAPEX/year
· Performance:
  · PV Degradation: 0.5% per year
  · Electrolyzer System Efficiency: 50 kWh/kg H₂ (LHV)
  · Haber-Bosch Efficiency: 90% (H₂ to NH₃)

B.2 Sensitivity Analysis: Green Ammonia Production Cost
The table below shows the impact of key variables on the levelized cost of green ammonia production in an integrated hub (Model: 1 GW Hybrid plant → Electrolysis → Ammonia synthesis).

Table B.1: Sensitivity of Green Ammonia Cost ($/ton)

Variable Base Case Low Case (Favorable) High Case (Unfavorable) Impact on Cost ($/ton)
Renewable CAPEX As per B.1 -20% +20% -85 / +85
Electrolyzer CAPEX $500/kW $350/kW $700/kW -50 / +70
WACC 7% 5% 9% -60 / +75
Capacity Factor (Hybrid Plant) 55% 60% 50% -55 / +60
Carbon Price (CBAM) $100/ton CO₂ $150/ton $50/ton +50 (Advantage) / -25

Interpretation: The model is most sensitive to the cost of capital (WACC) and the renewable plant’s capacity factor, underscoring the need for de-risking finance and optimal site selection.

B.3 Project Finance Model: 500 MW Anchor Tenant Project
A simplified 20-year pro-forma model for a 500 MW hybrid plant dedicated to OCP ammonia production shows the following key outputs under base case assumptions:

· Total Project CAPEX: ~$1.1 Billion (400 MW PV + 100 MW Wind + 200 MW Electrolyzer + Synthesis plant).
· Debt/Equity Structure: 70/30.
· Revenue: Based on a 20-year, take-or-pay PPA for green ammonia, indexed at 90% of the forward grey ammonia price (providing a stable floor).
· Key Outputs:
  · Project IRR (Equity): 10.5%
  · Project IRR (Project): 7.8%
  · Debt Service Coverage Ratio (DSCR, avg.): 1.45x
  · Payback Period: 9 years

